parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument cluster can cause the gauges to malfunction or fail, leading to a loss of critical information for the driver, such as speed, fuel level, and engine temperature, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The speedometer
fuel gauge
temperature gauge
and RPM gauge may malfunction or fail
causing the gauges to stick
fluctuate erratically
or not function at all.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various components to malfunction or fail, leading to a loss of critical functions, such as the ability to start the vehicle, operate the windows, or use the horn, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The electrical system may cause the windows to malfunction
the horn to fail
or the vehicle to shut off while driving
and may also cause the instrument cluster to malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the vehicle to lose steering control, making it difficult to maneuver and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle does not turn when steering
the vehicle dies while turning
loss of electrical power
loud clunking noise when trying to restart the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The seizure of the engine can cause the vehicle to stall or die while driving, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle shuts off while driving
loud clunking noise when trying to restart the vehicle
engine failure despite having sufficient oil.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to lose power, making it difficult to control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle shuts off while driving
loss of electrical power
loud clunking noise when trying to restart the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose stopping power, making it difficult to control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Brake pads fail
brakes squeak
vehicle bounces or rocks forward when parking and stopping
vehicle bounces or rocks backward at stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the tires can cause the vehicle to lose control, making it difficult to maneuver and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Tires warp
crack
or fray apart.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty fuel gauge can cause the driver to run out of fuel unexpectedly, leading to safety risks, inconvenience, and potential accidents.
symptoms: The fuel gauge displays erratic or incorrect readings
shows full or half full when the tank is almost empty
or gets stuck on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty speedometer can cause the driver to be unaware of their actual speed, leading to potential accidents, traffic violations, and safety risks.
symptoms: The speedometer gets stuck
displays incorrect readings
or shows an incorrect speed while the vehicle is stationary.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty power window can cause inconvenience and distraction while driving, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The power window only goes up an inch at a time
takes a long time to close
or has difficulty closing.
